 <H1>Summary</H1> 
 <P><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Disks provide cheap, non-volatile storage.
</H2></P>

<P><UL></P>

<P><LI>Random access, but cost depends on location of page on disk; important to arrange data sequentially to minimize seek and rotation delays.
</UL></UL><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Buffer manager brings pages into RAM.
</H2></P>

<P><UL></P>

<P><LI>Page stays in RAM until released by requestor.
<LI>Written to disk when frame chosen for replacement (which is sometime after requestor releases the page).
<LI>Choice of frame to replace based on replacement policy.
<LI>Tries to pre-fetch several pages at a time.</UL></UL></P>

